(5. Independent Study Guidance) Tj
T*
(For independent study, the learner should revisit the explanation and then practise with) Tj
T*
(tasks that reflect agreement correction exercises. The most effective habit is to read) Tj
T*
(the worked example slowly, restate each step in simple words, and then attempt a similar) Tj
T*
(question alone. This turns Concord into something the student can genuinely study and) Tj
T*
(understand without depending completely on a teacher.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key Ideas To Remember) Tj
T*
(- Concord should first be understood as a language idea before it is treated as an exam) Tj
T*
(topic.) Tj
T*
(- The learner must understand subject-verb agreement and consistency in structure) Tj
T*
(because it controls how questions in Concord are answered correctly.) Tj
T*
(- A strong answer in Concord uses the correct interpretation or writing method and) Tj
T*
(explains why that method fits the task.) Tj
T*
(- Correcting a sentence where subject and verb do not match is the type of application) Tj
T*
(that helps move the topic from explanation to mastery.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step-By-Step Method) Tj
T*
(1. Read the question or example and identify the part connected to Concord.) Tj
T*
(2. Recall the specific rule, process, or principle behind subject-verb agreement and) Tj
T*
(consistency in structure.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct interpretation or writing method step by step instead of jumping to) Tj
T*
(the answer.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the result carefully and confirm that it matches the requirement of the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on correcting a sentence where subject and verb do not) Tj
T*
(match.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in subject-verb agreement and consistency in structure that) Tj
T*
(the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Concord step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on agreement correction exercises.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid being distracted by nearby words instead of the true subject) Tj
T*
(while solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
